{
  "text": "Let P 3 (k) be the number of odd lines of length k in [CITATION_1] n , related to the density p 3 (k) by P 3 (k) = n k 4 n\u2212k p 3 (k). If each line of length k could be expressed M (k) times as L \u2022 \u2113 j , we would have the inequality (11) M (k)P 3 (k) + M (2k)P 3 (2k) + M (3k)P 3 (3k) + M (4k)P 3 (4k) \u2264 14|L k |.",
  "correct_citation": {
